Sentencas: Direct carbon solid oxide fuel cell (DC-SOFC) is a potential and prospective technology to convert chemical energy from real-world coal fuels into electricity with environment friendliness and high efficiency.
Titulo: A vanadium-doped La0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ perovskite as a promising anode of direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells for brown coal utilization

Sentencas: However, the limited three-phase reaction boundaries and the challenge of sluggish carbon oxidation ac-tivity have always hindered the development and application of DC-SOFCs.
Titulo: A vanadium-doped La0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ perovskite as a promising anode of direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells for brown coal utilization

Sentencas: On this account, here vanadium-doped B-site-deficient La0.5Sr0.5FeO3-delta (LSFVx, x = 0, 0.05, 0.10, 0.15) perovskite materials are synthesized and developed as the anode of DC-SOFCs for brown coal utilization.
Titulo: A vanadium-doped La0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ perovskite as a promising anode of direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells for brown coal utilization

Sentencas: The best electrochemical performance at 850 ? belongs to the LSFV0.1 cell, delivering a maximum power density of 249 mW cm(-2), and the lowest polarization resistance of 0.37 omega cm(2),along with the longest discharging time up to 8.65 h.
Titulo: A vanadium-doped La0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ perovskite as a promising anode of direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells for brown coal utilization

Sentencas: Compared with the pure LSF, the electrochemical performances of all perovskites doped with vanadium have been greatly promoted, demonstrating that the doping of vanadium can effectively expand the three-phase reaction boundaries of the cell, thus enhance the catalytic activity due to the promotion of oxygen deficiencies and tailing of electronic structures.(c) 2022
Titulo: A vanadium-doped La0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ perovskite as a promising anode of direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells for brown coal utilization
